quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
  43,34,"And for their houses, doors (of silver), and thrones (of silver) on which they could recline,",""
  43,35,"And adornments of gold. Yet all this (i.e. the roofs, doors, stairs, elevators, thrones of their houses) would have been nothing but an enjoyment of this world. And the Hereafter with your Lord is (only) for the Muttaqûn.<sup>2</sup>","[2] (V.43:35) Al-Muttaqûn: means the pious believers of Islamic Monotheism who fear Allâh much (abstain from all kinds of sins and evil deeds which He has forbidden) and love Allâh much (perform all kinds of good deeds which He has ordained)."
  43,36,"And whosoever turns away blindly from the remembrance of the Most Gracious (Allâh) (i.e. this Qur’ân and worship of Allâh), We appoint for him Shaitan (Satan - devil) to be a Qarîn (a companion) to him.",""
  43,37,"And verily, they (Satans / devils) hinder them from the Path (of Allâh), but they think that they are guided aright!",""
  43,38,"Till, when (such a one) comes to Us, he says [to his Qarîn (Satan / devil companion)] ""Would that between me and you were the distance of the two easts (or the east and west)"" - a worst (type of) companion (indeed)!",""
  43,39,"It will profit you not this Day (O you who turn away from Allâh’s remembrance and His worship) as you did wrong, (and) that you will be sharers (you and your Qarîn ) in the punishment.",""
  43,40,"Can you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) make the deaf to hear, or can you guide the blind or him who is in manifest error?",""
  43,41,"And even if We take you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) away, We shall indeed take vengeance on them.",""
  43,42,"Or (if) We show you that wherewith We threaten them: then verily We have perfect command over them.",""
  43,43,"So hold you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) fast to that which is revealed to you. Verily you are on the Straight Path.",""
  43,44,"And verily this (the Qur’ân) is indeed a Reminder for you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) and your people (Quraish people, or your followers), and you will be questioned (about it).",""
  43,45,"And ask (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم) those of Our Messengers whom We sent before you: ""Did We ever appoint âlihâh (gods) to be worshipped besides the Most Gracious (Allâh)?""",""
  43,46,"And indeed We did send Mûsâ (Moses) with Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) to Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) and his chiefs (inviting them to Allâh’s religion of Islâm) He said: ""Verily, I am a Messenger of the Lord of the ‘Âlamîn (mankind, jinn and all that exists).""",""
  43,47,"But when he came to them with Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations) behold, they laughed at them.",""
